Based on my comprehensive research, here are my architectural recommendations for your frontend UI components:

---

# Frontend UI Architecture Recommendations

## 1. Web App Frontend

### Framework Selection: React + Next.js

**Recommendation: Next.js 15 with React 19**

| Framework | Bundle Size | Performance | Ecosystem | Recommendation |
|-----------|-------------|-------------|-----------|----------------|
| React/Next.js | ~40KB | Good (Virtual DOM) | Largest | **Best for this use case** |
| Vue/Nuxt | ~20KB | Good | Strong | Good alternative |
| Svelte/SvelteKit | ~1.6KB | Best | Growing | Consider for CEP panel |

**Rationale:**
- Largest ecosystem for audio/media components
- Best library support for waveform visualization (wavesurfer.js)
- TanStack Query has first-class React support
- Easier to hire developers
- Server Components for optimal performance

### Component Library: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui

**Recommendation: shadcn/ui (80+ components)**

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

**Why shadcn/ui over alternatives:**

| Library | Bundle Impact | Customization | Accessibility |
|---------|---------------|---------------|---------------|
| **shadcn/ui** | Zero runtime (Tailwind only) | Full ownership of code | Built on Radix UI |
| Material UI | ~90KB+ | Theme overrides | Good |
| Chakra UI | ~50KB+ | Style props | Excellent |

Key benefits:
- Copy-paste model gives full control over component code
- Built on Radix UI primitives for accessibility
- Compatible with React 19 and Tailwind v4
- No runtime CSS-in-JS overhead
- Dark mode support built-in

### State Management Architecture

